[[File:Entada abyssinica00.jpg|thumb|<center>''[[Entada abyssinica]]''</center>]] [[File:Cnestis polyphylla00.jpg|thumb|<center>''[[Cnestis polyphylla]]''</center>]] '''André Revillon d'Apreval''', aka '''A. d'Apreval''', was a French botanical illustrator and lithographer, active 1875-1910, and known for his images in ''Plantae Davidianae'' (1884–88), ''Illustrationes Florae Insularum Maris Pacifici'' (1886-92) and ''Histoire physique, naturelle et politique de Madagascar'' (1882).<ref>'The Art of Botanical Illustration: An Illustrated History' - Wilfrid Blunt, William Thomas Stearn (Collins, London 1950)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://fr.artprice.com/artiste/433929/ar-d'apreval|title=A.R. D'APREVAL (act.1875-1910) : Ventes aux enchères, prix, indices et biographie pour A.R. D'APREVAL - Artprice.com|first=Thierry|last=EHRMANN|website=fr.artprice.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gw.geneanet.org/pierfit?lang=en;p=andre;n=revillon+d+apreval;type=tree|title=Build Your Family Tree, Share Your Family History and Improve Your Genealogy Research|website=Geneanet}}</ref> [[Henri Ernest Baillon]], the French physician and botanist, and main contributor to ''Histoire physique, naturelle et politique de Madagascar'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/bibliography/296#/summary|title=Details - Histoire naturelle des plantes / - Biodiversity Heritage Library|website=www.biodiversitylibrary.org}}</ref> named a new genus ''d'Aprevalia'' after him in 1884,<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/11016993#page/21/mode/1up|title=Bulletin mensuel de la Société linnéenne de Paris.|first1=Soci&#233;t&#233; Linn&#233;enne de|last1=Paris.|first2=Soci&#233;t&#233; Linn&#233;enne de|last2=Paris.|publisher=|volume=v. 1(52-81) 1884-86}}</ref> no doubt in honour of his illustrating the work, but the name was later placed under ''[[Delonix]]'' by [[René Paul Raymond Capuron]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tropicos.org/Name/40018090|title=Tropicos - Name - Aprevalia Baill.|website=www.tropicos.org}}</ref><ref>http://www.amjbot.org/content/92/8/1359.full</ref> A number of species such as ''[[Commiphora aprevalii]]'' (Baill.) Guillaumin, were named to commemorate him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theplantlist.org/tpl1.1/record/kew-2733408|title=Commiphora aprevalii (Baill.) Guillaumin — The Plant List|website=www.theplantlist.org}}</ref>
